abstract: HOT SPRINGS, Va., March 30-- When President Carter delivered his surefire, this-can't-miss, now-we'vegot-it anti-inflation plan No. 4 to an adoring audience of Administration officials at the White House on March 14, it was noted in this space that he seemed curiously uncomfortable with his text.

HALLANDALE, Fla., March 29-- Plugged Nickle laughed at the pretenders in the $175,000 Florida Derby today, winning Gulfstream Park's gaudiest race as he pleased and establishing himself, perhaps, as the horse to beat in the Kentucky Derby May 3.

abstract: FOR those New Jerseyans who have waited long periods for  buses to take them to and from work, it probably will not come as a surprise that a Federal transportation analyst has found that a lack of planning in 10 counties is responsible for much of the state's difficulties.

COSTA MESA, Calif., March 29 (AP) --Jo Ann Washam and Debbie Massey, overcoming conditions that frustrated most of the field, tied for the thirdround lead today at one-over-par 214 in the $150,000 Ladies' Professional Golf Association Kemper open.

abstract: THE eight days from Palm Sunday through Easter Sunday are  the most dramatic of the entire Christian church year. Holy Week is theoretically a time for Christian mourning, but music lovers of all faiths welcome it for the outpouring of fine musical works, great and small, that it brings.
